(2, 'Crystal Seeding', 'dimensions variable', 'Sound Co-production: C-LAB Taiwan Sound Lab, Center for Sound Arts and Acoustics Research, NTUA', '<p>"Crystal Seeding," created by three artists—HSU Chia-Wei, CHENG Hsien-Yu, and CHANG Ting-Tong, is a collaborative project with Taisugar’s Huwei Sugar Factory. Sucrose being the inspirational departure point, the project addresses Taiwanese puppet theatre, experimental music, sugar 3D printing, and robotic arms, through whose intertwined complexity the history of a small town in the last century is investigated.</p><p>The sugar industry was among the first to witness early modernization in Taiwan. An industrial sugar factory with machinery a hundred years ago could be considered unprecedented cutting-edge technology almost equivalent to today’s semiconductor industry. In 1907, Dai Nippon Sugar Manufacturing Co. built the Huwei Sugar Factory, one that produced the most sugar in this country at the time. With the introduction of industrialized factories, new industrial towns started to appear in Chiayi-Tainan Plain. Huwei Township was then transformed into the most modernized city/town in Southern Taiwan. Railroads, European-style gardens, iron bridges demonstrated the latest ideas about modernity. Because of the outbreak of the Pacific War, Huwei Sugar Factory was later expanded for ethanol production. The alcoholic fermentation converting sugars into energy and producing ethanol provided the fuel to Kamikaze, the Japanese Special Attack Unit, and resulted in the destructive bombing attacks at the factory. The sugar industry dwindled after the war, and the town was no longer up and coming. Consequently, the buildings of the sugar factory became desolated.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;The multi-channel video installation tells a narrative adapted from Japanized puppet theatre piece "Kurama Tengu" performed by the Sheng Ping Puppet Troupe. Through merging reality and fictionality, the project illustrates the history of Huwei Township. Moreover, the recorded performance of composer HUI Tak-Cheung in the sugar factory, interspersed in the video, turns the factory into site-specific “musical instruments.” In a theatre-like setting, a robotic arm, a 3D printer, and flag carrier emblems are all actors in this play who enter the stage as the narrative unfolds, and play various “roles” as well as demonstrate different “incidents” on stage.</p>', 'Longyan sugarcane field_In 1935, Dai-Nippon Sugar Co., Ltd. established the "Longyan Sugar Refinery" here, and it was also the last sugar factory established during the Japanese occupation. However, because of the low efficiency and low yield, they decided to merge into the Huwei Sugar Factory in 1968. The sugarcane grown here will be transported back to the Huwei Sugar Factory.｜Narrow-gauge train with a track gauge of 2 ft 6 in (762 mm) arrived at Huwei Sugar Factory with sugarcane_Although there are still two sugar factories in Taiwan, Yunlin Huwei and Tainan Shanhua are operating nowadays, the remaining 16 km that narrow-gauge railways with a track gauge of 2 ft 6 in (762 mm) carried the sugarcane are from Huwei to Baozhong.｜The Baozhong Branch Station_The Baozhong Branch Station of the Radio Taiwan International is a shortwave transmission substation in Yunlin that equipped with multiple transmitters. The radio waves are transmitted to the ionosphere at an elevation angle, transmitted to the target area by reflection, covering China, Northeast Asia, Southeast Asia, and other regions. Because it leased the land of Taiwan Sugar Company, the radio station retains the sugar factory’s building in the 1960s.｜Inside the Huwei Sugar Factory 1_This is the heater and evaporator. Five orange-coloured evaporation tanks are used to concentrate sugarcane juice into 65 degree brix syrup.｜Inside the Huwei Sugar Factory 2_This is the sugarcane crusher mill and the compression machine. The sugarcane crusher mill is responsible for shredding, tearing the sugarcane into fibres, and destroying the original cells to expose the sugar. It is the most critical machine before compression, and it will directly affect the extraction rate of sugarcane juice. The compression machine follows the principle of hydraulic pressure to compress all the sugar out of the sugarcane, and it will be compressed four times in total.｜Huwei sugar refinery alcohol tank_The by-product "molasses" produced by sugar can be used as a raw material to produce alcohol, significantly increasing the value of molasses. In 1926, the sugar factory obtained permission to set up an alcohol factory and began manufacturing in the same year. The machinery was a Guillaume system distillation machine, which was the largest alcohol factory in Asia at that time. Later, due to obsolete equipment, low efficiency and high costs, the annual loss was immense. It was demolished in 1975, leaving only two of the four chimneys and the remaining brick storage tank of the original spectacular factory.', 'mechanical, five-channel video, 3D printing installations', 'Crystal Seeding
mechanical, five-channel video, 3D printing installations
dimensions variable
2021', 'Exhibition view', 'Exhibition view', 'Exhibition view', 'Exhibition view'),
(5, 'Future Moshing, Datamosh !', '-', '', '<p><br/></p><p>《Signals from the Future》/ single-channel video / 2020<br/>《Let Me Fix You》/ single-channel audio performance / 2021<br/>《Where is LOVE》/ on-site graffiti (in Mandarin Chinese), light installation / 2021</p><p>The three projects exhibited in the venue, with hypertexts linking to the act of Moshing and Datamosh, are all based upon two foundational axes—channels of amateur internet celebrities on social media and certain warning messages. Through rearranging the performed experience in which the artist plays a role and claims that she has come back from the future, varied aspects of time-travel performances are reconstructed.&nbsp;</p><p><span style="color: var(--primary-gray-color);">In “Signals from the Future,” Betty Apple herself and different gender roles simulated by artificial intelligence are looked upon with the lens of social media’s sci-fi effect filters as signals that indicate traveling. On the other hand, “Let Me Fix You” adopts the sci-fi first-person narrative when ASMR is used “to fix robots,” which speaks well to the memes created by the AI mermaid cyborg. They both address the distortion of information that happens during the back-and-forth Moshing in space and time via the use of Datamosh as if it were a manifesto of Digital Impressionism passionately performing the dance in the data universe.</span></p>', '《Let Me Fix You》/ single-channel audio performance / 2021｜《Signals from the Future》/ single-channel video / 2020｜《Where is LOVE》/ single-channel audio performance, on-site graffiti (in Mandarin Chinese), light installation / 2021', 'single-channel video, single-channel audio performance, on-site graffiti (in Mandarin Chinese), light installation', 'Future Moshing, Datamosh!
